comments.comment_text:
Once you travel internationally
, if you are in charge of carrying your own luggage for all your transportation;
I believe a majority will pack lighter on the next trip. I am a shopper, I look up ahead of time in the larger areas ￼we will be visiting to find the closest MAILBOXETC. ￼ It doesn’t happen every trip.. but I ship items that I have bought if they will make my luggage too heavy. I make a list of what is going to be in the box and they wrap it, pack it and ship it home for you. I’ve always had great success using them. Yes, it does cost, but that way I’m not lugging around an extra suitcase full of items that I have bought.
